Name: Master Grade® Scope Mounting & Bore Sighting Kit - Real Avid
Description:
Precision scope alignment and quick bore sighting

\nThe Master Grade® Scope Mounting & Bore Sighting Kit is a comprehensive solution for precision scope alignment and bore sighting. This kit includes the Level-Right® Pro for accurate scope alignment, the Smart-Torq® torque driver for precise tightening and the Viz-Max Bore Sighter® for quick and easy bore sighting. Compatible with standard barrel and Picatinny rail attachments, this kit ensures optimal performance and accuracy. With step-by-step instructions provided, achieving perfect alignment and sighting is effortless. Upgrade your firearm optics experience with Master Grade tools. \n

Name: Smart-Fit® AR15 Vise Block - Real Avid
Description:
LOWER RECEIVER BLOCK THAT ADJUSTS FOR A ROCK SOLID FIT

\nThe Smart-Fit AR15 Vise Block is a revolutionary tool in firearm maintenance, designed to fit all MIL-SPEC AR15 magwells. Its adjustable design eliminates instability issues common with traditional gun vise blocks and can be used with an inverted lower receiver for easy access when building out lower receivers. It also provides a steady base for installing or removing buffer tubes. \n \nThe vise block features practical enhancements such as an oversized edge for improved grip in vises and a knurled texture that enhances overall grip during use. A magazine lock feature securely holds the lower receiver in place during maintenance tasks, providing additional stability and security. The Smart-Fit AR15 Vise Block sets new standards in firearms maintenance tools by offering comprehensive solutions tailored towards making these processes easier, safer and more efficient. \n
\n

Product Features

\n
\n
\n
\n
    \n
  • Adjustable-Fit: Accommodates all MIL-SPEC AR15 magwells, ensuring a secure and snug fit.
    • \n
  • Versatility: Can be used with an inverted lower receiver for easy access when building.
    • \n
  • Steady Base: Provides a steady base for installing or removing buffer tubes.
    • \n
  • Oversized Edge: Designed for improved grip in vises, reducing chances of accidental slips or drops.
    • \n
  • Knurled Texture: Enhances overall grip during use, increasing safety and efficiency.
    • \n
  • Magazine Lock Feature: Securely holds the lower receiver in place during maintenance tasks, providing additional stability and security.
    • \n
  • Eliminates Guesswork: The adjustment handle ensures a precise fit each time you use it.
    • \n
  • Durable Construction: Made from robust materials that can withstand heavy use without compromising performance or integrity.
    • \n
  • Comprehensive Solution: More than just a vise block – it's designed to make maintaining and building AR15 rifles easier, safer and more efficient.

  • Innovative Design & Functionality: Sets new standards in firearms maintenance tools by offering unmatched precision when working on your firearm.

Name: Bore-Max® Speed Jags™ & Patches Multi-Cal Pack - Real Avid
Description:
CLEAN BORES FASTER

\nThe Bore-Max Speed Jags & Patches Multi-Cal Pack heralds a new era in firearm maintenance, delivering up to 4x more bore contact for superior cleaning results. This comprehensive system includes ten specially designed jags for both handguns and rifles, covering an impressive range of calibers from .22 to .45 for handguns and .22/.223 to .30/7.62mm for rifles. Each jag is nickel-plated, ensuring longevity and resistance to chemical breakdown. Paired perfectly with these jags are the Speed Jag Patches, engineered from micro-pore fibers to offer superior absorbency and a grit-grabbing surface texture. The patches are uniquely designed to conform to the jags, avoiding the issue of bunching and thus enabling deeper and faster cleaning of your bore. Together, this caliber-specific set brings efficiency to a new level, saving you both time and effort while ensuring your firearms are maintained in peak condition. Use caution: Speed Jags and Speed Jag Patches are compatible exclusively with each other and should not be used with standard jags or patches to prevent damage or less effective cleaning. \n
\n

Product Features

\n
\n
\n
\n
    \n
  • Integrated system specifically designed for caliber-specific bore cleaning, including ten distinct jags, 4 for handguns and 6 for rifles.
    • \n
  • Nickel-plated jags ensure increased chemical resistance, contributing to longevity and consistent performance.
    • \n
  • Precision engineering of jags facilitates up to four times the bore contact area compared to conventional cleaning jags.
    • \n
  • Enhanced bore contact area allows efficient removal of fouling, copper and carbon deposits, reducing the number of required cleaning passes.
    • \n
  • Micro-pore fiber construction of patches provides high absorbency levels for effective solvent and lubricant application.
    • \n
  • Grit-grabbing surface texture of patches improves fouling removal during the cleaning process.
    • \n
  • Patches are dimensioned precisely to fit corresponding jags, ensuring optimal caliber-specific fitment and minimizing bunching.
    • \n
  • Mutual compatibility between jags and patches is crucial; designed to work in tandem for maximized cleaning efficiency.
    • \n
  • Use of incompatible components can result in suboptimal cleaning and may lead to bore damage.
    • \n
  • Strict adherence to compatibility guidelines is strongly recommended for optimal bore cleaning results.
    • \n
\n
\n
Categories: Real Avid, Tools

\nThe Real Avid Speed Stand is designed to make gun cleaning and modification tasks easier and more efficient. It is compact, lightweight and portable, making it perfect for use at home or at the range. The adjustable feet provide a solid foundation on uneven surfaces, while the Gun Gripper™ technology securely holds your firearm in place during cleaning or modification. The Speed Stand's collapsible design allows for easy storage and transportation, and its adjustable footprint ensures a perfect fit for all rifles and shotguns. Whether you're a professional gunsmith or a firearm enthusiast, the Speed Stand is a must-have tool that will make your gun cleaning and modification tasks faster and more convenient. \n

\n
\n
\n
\n \nThe Tyrant Designs CNC Glock 43 & 43x Compensator, known as the Glock 43 T-Comp, dramatically reduces muzzle rise and sensed recoil, allowing much quicker target re-acquisition. Compatible with ½-28 threaded barrels our compensator requires no modification to your 9mm Glock.. The G43 T-Comp works on all Glock 43's including the 43x and will function using almost any grain ammunition. \n \nThe real enginuity is in how the T-Comp is installed. Utilizing a two piece design our Glock comp installs securely in seconds WITHOUT the need for set screws or any other faulty attachment methods. Working on a concept focused on uncompromised innovation allowed considerable engineering freedom in developing significant solutions. Once attached, the Tyrant Compensator will not come loose while operating your firearm, or while holstering/unholstering it. Whether you are a range day goer or competitive shooter we are confident our Glock compensator not only outperforms the competition but sets a new standard for compensator innovation. \n \n

Name: Inforce WMLX White / IR - Gen 3
Description:

    \n
    • \n
\n
\n
\n
\n
\n
\n
\n
\n \nINFORCE has launched its latest iteration of weapon mounted lights with the WMLX White/IR Gen 3. The newest generation boasts superior brightness and power, providing more than twice the beam intensity of its predecessor on two 123a batteries. The 2-hour battery life remains unchanged, ensuring consistent performance for extended use in the field. \n \nWith a beam intensity of 900 lumens and a range of 656ft/200m, the WMLX White/IR Gen 3 offers exceptional visibility within a comfortable engagement range. This feature, combined with its ergonomic nonslip button, contoured to the shape of the human thumb, ensures that users can activate and deactivate the light intuitively and safely. Additionally, a flip safety prevents the device from being turned on until the user is ready. \n \nThe WMLX White/IR Gen 3 is suitable for close quarter engagements when mounted to a shotgun or pistol-caliber carbine, as well as mid-range shooting when clipped onto a rifle. Its construction with glass reinforced nylon, which is impervious to dirt, sand, or other solid debris, sets it apart from other models that may use cheaper plastic. The model is also waterproof up to 66 feet/20 meters, ensuring reliable performance in any conditions. \n \nThis lightweight and durable rifle light is perfect for any rifleman or hunter, and its exceptional features serve as a testament to INFORCE's commitment to quality and reliability. The WMLX White/IR Gen 3 is a valuable addition to any weapon system for anyone who demands superior illumination and performance. \n \nFeatures \n
    \n
  • 900 Lumen output on high mode
    • \n
  • 10,000 candela beam intensity
    • \n
  • IR Output 1W
    • \n
  • Distance of 656 feet (200m)
    • \n
  • Battery life of 2hrs on two 123a batteries (1.5 hours on IR mode)
    • \n
  • ¼ turn of the head engages lockout mode for travel, transport & storage
    • \n
  • Safety lever minimizes accidental discharge
    • \n
  • Integrated clamp interfaces with MIL-STD-1913 rails
    • \n
  • No tools required for setup or takedown
    • \n
  • Non-slip switch controls constant, momentary, and strobe functions
    • \n
  • Black or Flat Dark Earth finish
    • \n
  • Waterproof up to 66ft/20m
    • \n

Name: FOBUS IWB/Appendix Ambidextrous Holster for sig P365
Description:
\n

About the Holster

\n
APN is an IWB and OWB holster designed for appendix carry or standard I/OWB carry on your waist. The holster is offered with an adjustment screw for accurate retention pressure and personal preference; a belt clip/J hook that allows five cant positions with a simple turn clockwise/counterclockwise; a sweat guard to buffer between the firearm and your body, to assist with better purchase of the firearm and to offer a degree of ventilation, without allowing sweat to pass to the slide of your firearm (the sweat guard is detachable and you may use the holster without it); a concealment wing (available for right-handed only) to push the grip of your firearm towards your body for less 'printing' (also removable); a rigid paddle that enables to carry the holster as OWB; and finally, the holster is ambidextrous and may be switched to left-hand use without any tools required.  The APN holster is highly concealable, very lightweight, completely washable, ventilated, highly durable, it is contoured for maximum comfort, and is extremely convenient for every day concealed carry.
\n
\n
\n

How to use 

\n
\n \nPlace the holster inside your pants, in a location of your preference. The holster may be used for appendix carry or for standard IWB carry on your waist. Make sure the belt clip is outside your pants and over your belt, while its lower hook is catching the belt from underneath. \n \nIf using a J hook (belt clip), make sure it goes first over your pants (between your pants and the backside of your belt) and then catches the belt from underneath. If using a paddle, make sure to dismantle the belt clip, sweat-guard, and concealment wing first. Then click the paddle into the sweat-guard location. Place the holster on your hip and make sure the paddle is pushed all the way down on your belt. \n \n
\n
\n
\n \n  *The J hook is discontinued \n \n  \n

Technical Information

\nHolster Material: a mixture of mold injected Polymers. Passive retention with adjustment screw: Fobus passive retention system acts like a spring on the trigger guard area and holds the gun firmly in place. \n \n
Categories: FOBUS, Holster, IWB - Holster Dalam, SIG SAUER

This Polymer Double mag holster fits 9MM .40 .45 Caliber Magazines Pouch Single or Double Stack Mag.for Glock 17/19/22/23/24/27/34/43/43x/45 magazines; Sig Sauer P226/P229/P365; S&W M&P 9mm/M&P 9mm Shield;Beretta APX/M9/92/Px4 storm;Taurus TH9/G2s/G2C/92;Springfield XD/XDS/XDM;Ruger EC9s/LC9s/SECURITY-9/Ruger TACerican Pistol;1911; Walther PPQ 45/PPQ M2/PPQ Classic/P99/PPS/PPS M2; CZ 75/P10 and more models, please check the Compatible Common Models. \n
    \n
  • 【Adjustable】--- Our Universal Double Magazine Pouch offers 3 adjustable points to keep a consistent tight, which is designed to reduce half of time of the adjustment. To adjust tension, simply loosen or tighten the screw, then adjust the components on both sides, which helps to save more time for accurate shooting.
    • \n
  • 【Paddle Holster】--- Paddle design securely slides on to pants or belt, and easy to take it off. Fully adjustable and 360degree rotation cant for all applications, so you can adjust it according to your withdraw angle.
    • \n
  • 【Long Lasting】--- The Mag Pouch is made of excellent Polymer Material that is not only waterproof, sweat - resistant but lightweight, durable and non-abrasive to firearm's finish. And the holster is with silica gel that can contact with the body directly.
    • \n
\n【Occasions】--- Designed for enduring the hardest operating conditions, the holster is an ideal equipment for military, courser, shooting coach, law enforcement agencies or personal protection use, such as airsoft events, shooting and so on.

Name: QuickLock single mounting Rail Platform for all Fobus Holsters & Magazine Pouches
Description:
MOLLE RP

\nThe Fobus MND (MOLLE) is designed to be mounted on all vests and backpacks with a standard pouch attachment ladder system (PALS). \n \nAttach your Fobus holster or pouch with the RPM device (Rail Platform Molle) to the MND using the Allen screw provided. \n \nMake sure to place the RPM device with the release button pointing to 11-10 o'clock (for right-hand users), while the cogwheel located at 6 o'clock. \n \n  \n

How to use

\nPaddle attachment: Tighten your belt. Place the RP on your hip and make sure the paddle is pushed all the way down onto your belt. \n \nBelt holder attachment: Slide your belt through the belt loops and adjust your belt accordingly. \n \nAttach the holster or pouch onto the RP's QuickLock rails by applying pressure, sliding and clicking into place. To detach press down on the lever and slide out. \n \n

Name: Fobus Beretta PX4 Storm Full Size holster
Description: BRCH RT (Roto) open holster type CH (trigger guard lock) from an Israeli company Fobus. Holster protects weapon from damage, does not tend to move. Made by injection molding from scratch-, impact- and temperature-resistant nylon, a high-density plastic material. Available for lawmanual. \n \nFor pistols: \nBeretta: PX4 Storm Full Size in all calibers \n \nType of holster - professional line CH focuses on security. Safety mechanism Trigger Guard Locking System (CH Rapid Release System) allows the weapon to be carried safely in the holster, preventing it from falling out during movement. The safety enforces a correct grip on the weapon when it is drawn. Profiled button Trigger Guard Locking System is located on the trigger guard area, securing the weapon inside the holster (from the outside). When the weapon is drawn, the index finger is over the trigger in the correct shooting position, which aids in performing procedures before firing the weapon. The safety feature makes it difficult to unauthorized removal of the weapon from the holster while moving through a crowd. \n \nMounting - RT (Rotating Paddle), rotating fin Roto 360° on the belt. Designed to fit as close as possible to the user's figure. Suitable for "undercover" work when discretion is an important consideration. Adjusting the angle of the holster. The handle allows you to adjust the angle of the holster. 360 degree rotation pinned equipment, angle setting (locking in one of 16 defined positions).
Categories: BERRETA, FOBUS, Holster, OWB - Holster Luar

Name: FOBUS Tactical Rotating Belt Holster for H&K P30L HS2000
Description: The Tactical Series is an active retention holster. To un-holster your firearm, unfasten the safety strap and rock the firearm back approximately one half on an inch followed by a deliberate upward motion. When re-holstering your firearm, insert the barrel first into the muzzle stud, snap the firearm into the holster and refasten the safety strap. \n \nAllows for carrying handguns with a light / laser mounted on the under-barrel rail. Open holster body design allows any light / laser system. Lightweight, reinforced polymer construction with polymer retaining strap. Unique hinge design allows for straight, upward draw. DO NOT USE the RBT Tactical Series holster without a tactical accessory attached to the firearm as it is designed to work only with the rail accessory attached. \n• Muzzle stud and polymer strap provide retention \n• Low profile for concealability \n• Lightweight compact design \n• Rubberized paddle backing for extra stability and comfort \n• Unique hinge design allows for straight, upward draw \n• Requires attachment of rail accessory

Description: The Eemann Tech Competition Sear for Colt 1911, 2011 and their clones. Available in Alloy Steel & Stainless Steel. \n \nThe Eemann Tech Competition Sear for Colt 1911, 2011 and their clones. \n \nMaterial: Alloy Steel / Stainless Steel 1.4034 (AISI 420) \nCaliber: All \n \nWorks perfectly with all Eemann Tech Competition Hammers. \n \nAll the EEMANN TECH parts for Colt 1911, STI 2011 and their clones are made from high quality carbon, alloyed or stainless steel using technologies and CNC machines of new generation. \n \n  \n \nNo fitting required and instant installation in most cases. Name: Eemann Tech Handgrip 90ml
Description: Eemann Tech Handgrip \n \nThe Eemann Tech Handgrip is designed to improve a shooter’s grip by removing moisture, sweat and oils from the hands. \n \nThe lotion dries quickly, and is long lasting. \n \nWhen applied, the handgrip leaves a thin layer of product on the hands without any flaking or powdering. \n \nThe Eemann Tech Handgrip comes in a convenient and long lasting 90ml size bottle. A mixing ball is included for thorough blending. \n \nAdvantages: \n• Enhances grip \n• Quick dry formula \n• Removes moisture \n• Long lasting 90ml bottle \n• Kills germs \n \nDirections for use: \nApply a small amount of the Eemann Tech Handgrip to the palms of the hands and spread evenly over the surface of the hands covering grip contact points. \n \nСaution: \n• Keep away from open flame \n• Best when stored below 30 degrees Celsius \n• Ensure container is properly sealed \n• For external use only \n• Avoid eye contact \n• In event of eye contact, rinse with water and seek medical attention \n \nIngredients: Ethanol, Water, Parfum Chlorhexidine Gluconate, Propylene Glycol, Magnesium Carbonate. \n \nKEEP OUT OF REACH OF CHILDREN \n \nCapacity: 90ml bottle
Categories: Cleaning Kits, Eemann Tech

Name: Eemann Tech Main Springs Calibration Pack for 1911/2011
Description: The Eemann Tech Main Springs Calibration Pack for 1911/2011 has been specially made for 1911 and 2011 pistols and their models. \n \nIt allows owners to choose the best suitable power of Main Spring for their firearms. \n \nThe pack includes a range of the most popular power Main Springs including 14,15,16,17 and 18 lbs. \n \nThe Eemann Tech main springs calibration pack is offered to allow the shooter a choice of Competition Main Springs to adjust the power of the Main Spring according to the individual needs of the competitor. \n \nMade of steel with thermic treatment for the best performance and quality! \n \nEvery Eemann Tech Main Spring for 1911/2011 has its own unique colour, allowing for visual identification of the power value throughout its whole service life period. \n \nAll springs are partially painted with polymer and heat-treated paint which remains flexible throughout the whole period of service. The paint does not ruin or dye the handgun from the inside. \n \nEach pack contains five competition-coloured main springs. \n \nPack includes: \n \n• ET-111160 – 14lbs – Eemann Tech Competition Main Spring for 1911/2011 – BLUE color – 1 pc. \n• ET-111161 – 15lbs – Eemann Tech Competition Main Spring for 1911/2011 – RED color – 1 pc. \n• ET-111162-  16lbs – Eemann Tech Competition Main Spring for 1911/2011 – GREEN color – 1 pc. \n• ET-111163 – 17lbs – Eemann Tech Competition Main Spring for 1911/2011 – YELLOW color – 1 pc. \n• ET-111164 – 18lbs – Eemann Tech Competition Main Spring for 1911/2011 – NO Color – 1 pc.
Categories: 1911, Accessories, Eemann Tech, Handguns, Accessories > Recoil Reduction Spring System

Name: Inforce WMLx White Gen 3
Description:
\n \nINFORCE has launched the latest weapon mounted light, the WMLX White Gen 3, which is a significant upgrade over its predecessor. This version is brighter and more powerful than ever before, boasting over twice the beam intensity on the same battery, without compromising on battery life, which remains at a solid 2 hours. With a beam intensity of 25,000 candelas on a 1,100 lumen bulb, the WMLX White Gen 3 emits an extremely bright light that is more than five times the amount needed to blind someone in broad daylight. With a range of 1,036.75 feet (316m), this weapon light is perfect for close quarter engagements when mounted to a shotgun or pistol-caliber carbine, or mid-range shooting when clipped onto a rifle. \n \nThe ergonomic nonslip button of the WMLX White Gen 3 is contoured to the shape of the human thumb, rendering tape switches of older designs obsolete. The button allows for intuitive activation and deactivation of the light, while a flip safety ensures that it cannot be accidentally turned on. INFORCE has constructed the WMLX White Gen 3 with glass reinforced nylon, making it impervious to dirt, sand, and other solid debris. The light is also waterproof up to 66 feet/20 meters. This lightweight and durable rifle light is perfect for hunters and riflemen and showcases INFORCE's dedication to quality, reliability, and customer satisfaction. \n \n
\n
\n

Features of INFORCE Gen 3 - WMLx 1100 Lumens Weapon Light

\n
    \n
  • 1/4 turn of the head engages lockout mode for travel, transport & storage
    • \n
  • Safety lever minimizes accidental discharge
    • \n
  • Integrated clamp interfaces with MIL-STD-1913 rails
    • \n
  • No tools required for setup or takedown
    • \n
  • Non-slip switch controls constant, momentary, and strobe functions
    • \n
\n
Categories: Flashlight & Laser, Inforce, Flashlight & Laser > Rifle Flashlight

Name: Eemann Tech Progressive Recoil Spring for 1911/2011
Description: The Eemann Tech Progressive Recoil Spring for 1911/2011 pistols and their clones. \n \nProgressive Recoil Spring differs from the common spring by the fact that the distance between coils keeps reducing starting from the middle of the spring till the last coil. \n \nWhile getting pressure the spring starts functioning in two phases: \n• 1st: The first half of the spring with identical distance between coils starts compressing from the beginning. \n• 2nd: After the first half has been fully shrunk the second half with reduced coil distance starts its compressing as well. \n \nEach coil increases the spring compression. Full compression provides maximum resistance and reduces recoil impulse. \n \nEvery Eemann Tech Recoil spring has its own unique colour that allows visual identification of the power value throughout its whole service life period. \n \nAll springs are painted with polymer heat treated paint which remains flexible throughout the whole period of service. The paint does not ruin or dye handgun from inside. \n \n
Categories: Accessories, Eemann Tech, Accessories > Recoil Reduction Spring System

Name: CR Speed Versa C-BAX "VERSA-POUCH"
Description:
Versa-Pouch \nThe Competition Proven Versa-Pouch takes its name from the Versatility it offers its users. Multi Mag Fit & Ambidextrous the Versa-Pouch is unlike any other Mag Pouch on the Market. Supplied with Inserts that can be added or removed to fit a wide variety of popular pistol magazines. The Versa-Pouch's ambidextrous design allows for Left or Right-handed shooters set-up. The Versa-Pouch is supplied with knurled aluminium“Wide Track” adjusters. for fast & precise retention adjustment. A generous Index finger slot on the front face of the Pouch ensures fast consistent mag changes. Apart from it’s Right and Left handed capability the angle adjustable Versa-Pouch can also be orientated in low or high orientation depending on user preference. All Versa-Pouches now feature the latest version Polymer C-Bax Hanger system for maximum inner & outer belt Velcro Contact, enhancing stability, comfort. \n \nQuality construction / Speedy Draws / Adjustable Retention / Fully Ambidextrous / Multi Mag Fit / Easy angle adjustment - "from one pouch" \n \nVersa-Pouch is supplied with 3X inserts Below to accept the following magazines - Standard - \n
    \n
  • High Cap - Insert -  STI, SV, SPS, 2011 & Clones as well as Para Ordnance, Bul M5 etc.
    • \n
  • BER / CZ- Insert - Most 9mm & 40 S&W Double Stack Mags incl. CZ75 / Shadow 1/2 Canik, Tanfoglio Stock 1/2/3
    • \n
  • GL - Insert  - All Small frame Glock mags. Sub-compact, compact & full-size 9MM & 40S&W models
    • \n
\n  \n \nVersa-Pouch is supplied with 5X inserts, Above & Below to accept the following magazines - Fully Loaded - \n
    \n
  • W/B - Insert - Modern Double Stack Mags - Incl. M&P / PX4 / SIG 320
    • \n
  • Single Stack - Insert - 1911 Single Stack & clones
    • \n

Name: AR15 4.8" R-ONE M-LOK Handguard - FDE Cerakote
Description:
The ATLAS R-ONE is the newest addition to the Aero Precision Handguard lineup. Machined from 6061-T6 Aluminum, the R-ONE line of handguards are designed with size and weight in mind, providing the perfect handguard for your lightweight build. Our proprietary ATLAS attachment system is a durable and dependable mounting platform, maintaining a slim profile while still providing the strength and stability customers have grown to love from Aero Precision handguards. \n \nAvailable in M-LOK profiles with 4.8", 7.3", 9.3", 10.3", 12.7" and 15" options. \n

ATLAS

\nThe new Aero Taper Lock Attachment System (ATLAS) is both functional and aesthetically pleasing. It features 2 mirrored tapered locking nuts that provide evenly distributed clamping pressure across a custom engineered barrel nut with use of a turnbuckle screw. A ratcheting detent further secures the design while providing positive registration during installation. By design, the even pressure of the ATLAS system avoids distortion of the handguard often seen with current applications during installation. \n \nAll hardware mounting parts are included with the purchase of an ATLAS Handguard. \n

Lightweight By Design

\n
    \n
  • M-LOK Handguard Weights: 4.8" - 3.9 oz / 7.3" - 5.22 oz / 9.3" - 6.03 oz / 10.3" - 6.7 oz / 12.7" - 8 oz / 15" - 9.07 oz
    • \n
  • Mounting Hardware Weight: 1.9 oz (same across all ATLAS Handguard options)
    • \n
\n

Features:

\n
    \n
  • Full top picatinny rail for optional attachments
    • \n
  • Quick disconnect sling socket at the 3, 6 and 9 o'clock positions
    • \n
  • Compatible with low profile gas blocks
    • \n
  • 1.3" Inside diameter
    • \n
  • 1.5" Outside diameter
    • \n
  • Compatible with mil-spec AR15 upper receivers and barrels
    • \n
  • NOT Compatible with M4E1 Enhanced Upper Receivers
    • \n
\nATLAS Handguards are designed to match seamlessly with our M4E1 Threaded Upper Receivers. Additionally, they are compatible with any Mil-Spec AR-15 upper receivers as well. However, they may not be compatible with billet upper receivers due to indexing tabs. Save when you buy them as a combo. \n \nPlease note: The ATLAS Handguards are NOT compatible with our M4E1 Enhanced Upper Receiver.
Categories: Aero Precision, Handguards & Rail System > Handguard-Mlok, Handguards & Rail System, Rifles

One Of The Most Commonly Used Duty Gear

\nDrop leg holster is mainly known as a heavy-duty gear, which is commonly used by military, police officers, SWAT teams, or Special Forces operator. It also can be found on special occasions like special shooting events, military fans dress up, and so on. \n \n \n

Made For Battlefield

Name: MAXIM DEFENSE CQB STOCK
Short description:
The Maxim Defense CQB Gen 7 stock For AR-15
\n

Like the Gen 6, the Gen 7 is a CQB stock built for comfort and durability for real-world use. No buttons to push, just pull the stock to deploy. At its most collapsed position, this CQB stock only adds 5.35” to your AR15. At full extension, the Maxim CQB stock is the length of an extended carbine stock. And with 4 total positions you can adjust for maximum comfort and multiple scenarios. Rapid deployment, purpose driven materials, and the functionality you need, the Maxim Defense CQB Stock is simply the most thought out, versatile, and durable CQB stock on the market.

\n

The Gen 7 is for those who want a sleeker profile, eliminating the side sling swivel attachment points from the housing. Instead, the Gen 7 comes with our ambidextrous sling mount already installed.

Name: Dead Foot Arms SCW 4 GEN2
Description:
Description

\n
\n
The SCW 4 kit is an extremely compact PDW Style stock/brace which utilizes the patented Dead Foot Arms LLC Modified Cycle System and any standard M16/9mm style bolt carrier group.
\n
\n
Collapsed length is 3.9″. While compact, it is still very versatile, allowing for button free stock deployment and 6 length of pull settings. At full extension, length reaches 12.6” from trigger, keeping it comfortable for shooters of all sizes.
\n
\n
The SCW 4 features an ergonomic design that uses dual rails that are offset to not interfere with weapon controls or function. System includes complete stock/brace assembly, receiver extension, adjustment rail, plunger/recoil springs, and plunger. System weight is 18 oz.
\n
\n
\n
*NOTE- this product does not require a shortened M16/9mm style BCG, thus no bolt carrier group is sold with this kit.
\n
\n
\n
Compatible with most Rifle Caliber AR-15 pistols and rifles in calibers of: .223, .223Wylde, 5.56, 300 BO, 7.62x39, 6.8 SPC, 6.5 Grendel, .458 SOCOM, 50 Beowulf. BCG needs to have an internal rear cavity of at least 0.62 inches in diameter to work with the MCS. For CMMG Radial Delay you will need to order the Rifle Caliber version.
\n
\n
Will work with most 9mm BCGs. BCG needs to have an internal diameter of at least 0.62 inches in diameter and have a removable weight that doesn't change the length of the bolt. 9mm BCGs that have a removable weight that reduces the overall length of the bolt are not compatible.
\n
Categories: Butt-Stocks, Buttstock, Buttstock > Buttstock-AR15

Name: ARISAKA Offset Optic Mount
Description: The Patented Arisaka Offset Optic Mount is a modular mounting solution that allows the user to select a 35 or 45 degree offset position for their red dot sight without additional components. The 35 degree position brings the red dot sight up closer to slimmer, smaller scopes, while the 45 degree position provides additional clearance around wider turrets. \n \nThe mount is set to 35 or 45 degrees by reversing the stem between the optic plate and base during assembly. The mount's unique geometry correctly aligns the optic vertically over the bore and maintains a consistent height at both 35 and 45 degrees. \n \nTwo heights of plates are offered; standard (1.5" to 1.8") and tall (1.9" to 2.2"). The base and optic plates can be reversed, making the mount fully ambidextrous. It is recommended that you choose the plate height that corresponds to your primary optic height. For example, if your scope is mounted in a 1.54” height mount, you’d choose the regular height plate for your offset red dot. This ensures a consistent cheek weld and seamless transition between your primary optic and offset red dot.
Categories: Mounting, Mounts & Sights Rifle

ARISAKA Side Scout Mount M-Lok
Description:
Description

\n
\n \nThe Arisaka Side Scout Mount (SSM) is designed for use with Surefire Scout Lights, the Modlite PLH and OKW weapon lights, the Arisaka 300, 600 and 18650 Series, the Streamlight Protac Rail Mount lights, and the Olight Odin. It replaces the stock Picatinny rail adapter with a low profile mount for M-Lok handguards, and tucks the light underneath either side of the ATPIAL laser/illuminator series, including the ATPIAL-C, AN/PEQ15, and LA-5/PEQ. It will also allow the light to clear an NGAL and the QD lever on the Steiner DBAL I2, A3, and D2. \n \nCompatible with the Modlite PLH, PLHv2 and OKW, Surefire M300A, M300B, M300C, M300V, M312, M322, M312V, M313V, M322V, M600B, M600C, M600P, M600U, M600V, M600DF, M612, M622, M603V, M612V, M622V, Streamlight Protac Rail Mount 1, 2 and HL-X (non-laser), Olight Odin, CD REIN, and Arisaka 300, 600 and 18650 Series. \n \nThe longer base Scout lights like the M620, M951/2 and M961/2 can be used with the Side Scout Mount with the addition of our Offset M620 adapter. \n \nAs a bonus, the Side Scout Mount also works nicely on the Sig MPX PCC and MCX Virtus M-Lok handguards. \n \nSKU: SSM-M \n \nLength: 1.265" \n \nThickness: 0.2" \n \nWeight: 0.6 oz \n \nThe mount is CNC machined from 6061-T651 aluminum and MIL-A-8625 Type III hard coat anodized. Includes necessary screws to attach light body to mount. Requires a T20 Torx or IP20 TorxPlus driver for installation (not included). A T9 Torx driver is required to remove the stock Picatinny mount from Surefire Scout Lights. Recommended torque: 30 inch lbs for M-Lok screws and 20 inch lbs for light body screws with medium strength threadlocker. \n \nHardware: Two M-Lok nuts, two 10-24x5/16" Torx button head screws, two 8-32x5/16" Torx flat head screws. \n \n
Categories: ARISAKA, Mounting, Mounts & Sights Rifle

Name: ARISAKA Rail Slider
Description:
Description

\n
\n \nMake Picatinny Great Again with the Patent Pending Arisaka Rail Slider. It transforms the Picatinny rail on your rifle into a multi-position sliding mount with a push button recoil lug. A unique detented knob is used to set sliding tension, accounts for out-of-spec rails, allows the mount to be removed or installed without having to slide it off the end of the rail, and can be quickly and easily tightened down for maximum precision. \n \nThe Rail Slider features the ARMS 17S pattern for compatibility with popular bipods like the Atlas PSR, Atlas CAL, MDT Cyke, and Magpul 17S Bipod. It can also be used with Harris swivel bipods by adding our 17-S Harris Bipod Adapter. \n \nAdditionally, we offer several ball head adapters so that the Rail Slider can be used on top of a tripod. In this arrangement the user can quickly drop a Picatinny railed rifle on top, or use our LRF/Spotter Adapter to mount spotting scopes, laser range finders, or any other compatible gear. \n \nWeight: 2.2 oz. \n \nThe Rail Slider is CNC machined from stainless steel and MIL-A-8625 Type III hard coat anodized 6061-T651 aluminum. Includes two 10-32 socket cap screws. Requires a 5/32 Allen wrench for installation (not included). Recommended torque: 30 inch lbs. \n \nThis product is covered by U.S. Patent No(s). D1028158 and other pending patents. \n \n
Categories: ARISAKA, Mounting, Mounts & Sights Rifle

\n \nThe Magpul M-LOK AFG (Angled Fore Grip) is the result of research and refinements done to the original AFG and AFG-2. By integrating the direct-attach M-LOK mounting system with minimalist construction, we were able to produce a high strength grip that only weighs 1.2 ounces, including hardware.  \n \nAllowing for a wider range of mounting location options, the M-LOK AFG is ¾" shorter than the AFG-2, while maintaining a similar gripping surface area. Even though the M-LOK AFG is more compact than its predecessors, it takes into account natural body mechanics to provide a comfortable and stable user interface that reduces fatigue and allows for more precise weapon control. By positioning the shooter's hand high on the centerline of the bore, unlike conventional vertical fore grips, the M-LOK AFG helps mitigate recoil and control the weapon to facilitate faster, more accurate follow-up shots. \n \nAll hardware necessary for attachment directly to M-LOK Slots on either aluminum or polymer hand guards and forends is included. \n \nMade in the USA. \n \n
